![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/bd32ee7f-623e-43ff-86a9-96e36dfef9cc/bw.jpg?format=original)

This week on the Major Issues Podcast, the hosts look back on the best and worst of 2025 across movies, television, and comics. From breakout hits that exceeded expectations to high-profile projects that completely missed the mark, nothing is off-limits as they sort through a year packed with big swings, bold ideas, and costly misfires.

The discussion spans superhero cinema, prestige TV, surprise successes, creative disappointments, and the comic runs that defined or derailed the year. What worked, what failed, and what it all says about where pop culture is headed next. It is a no-holds-barred year-in-review episode you will not want to miss.

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

Send us feedback at **ComicBookClique@Gmail.com!** You Are Worthy! 

